import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['source'], bins=50, alpha=0.5, label='Source')
    plt.hist(data['target'], bins=50, alpha=0.5, label='Target')
    plt.axvline(data['source'].mean(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Source')
    plt.axvline(data['target'].mean(), color='orange', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Target')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of module dependencies?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10 = data['source'].value_counts().nlargest(10)
    plt.bar(top_10.index, top_10.values)
    plt.title('What is the most common source module for dependencies?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Module ID')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Dependencies')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10_target_modules = data['target'].value_counts().nlargest(10)
    top_10_target_modules.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common target module for dependencies?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Module ID')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Dependencies')
    plt.legend(['Number of Dependencies'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['source'], data['target'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between source and target module IDs?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['num_dependencies'] = data.groupby('source')['target'].transform('count')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['num_dependencies'], vert=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Number of dependencies')
    ax.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["num_dependencies"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of dependencies per module?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
